incidentArtifactTypeDTO Data Type

Definition of an artifact type.

Namespace
(Default)
Properties
name data type type namespace min/max occurs description
desc string element 0/1 Description of the artifact type.
enabled boolean element 1/1 Is the artifact type enabled?
export_key string element 0/1 The key which uniquely identifies the object being imported
file boolean element 1/1 The value of an artifact of this type is a file. The artifact is created using IncidentArtifactREST resource.
multi_aware boolean element 1/1 When true, the value of an artifact of this is type is scanned, and if multiple artifact values are detected multiple artifacts are created from the single artifact.
name string element 0/1 Display name of the artifact type.
parse_as_csv boolean element 1/1 If true and the artifact type is mutli aware then the value is parsed using comma separated value format.
programmatic_name string element 0/1 This is the name used by scripting when referencing this artifact type. This is also can be used when referencing artifact types by ObjectHandle.
reg_exp string element 0/1 This is used to validate the value of artifacts of this type.
split_on string element 0/1 Splitter on pattern used with multiple values. This is a readonly property.
system boolean element 1/1 Is this artifact type pre-defined by the system. This is a read-only attribute.
use_for_relationships boolean element 1/1 If true this artifacts of this type are used for determining relationships to other incidents. Otherwise the artifact is not used for determining relationships.
uuid string element 0/1 The system UUID of the object used as a backup to detect renames

<incidentArtifactTypeDTO>

</incidentArtifactTypeDTO>
